==English==
===Etymology===
{{It.}} ''corridore'' (= ''[[corridoio]]'') long passage, from ''[[correre]]'', to run

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:Received Pronunciation|RP]] {{IPA|/ˈkɒrɪˌdɔː/}}, {{SAMPA|/"kQrI%dO:/}} ''or'' {{IPA|/ˈkɒrɪˌdə/}}, {{SAMPA|/"kQrI%d@/}}
*[[w:General American|GenAm]] {{AHD|kôrʹədôr'}}, {{IPA|/ˈkɔrəˌdɔr/}}, {{SAMPA|/"kOr@%dOr/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A [[narrow]] [[hall]] or [[passage]] with [[room]]s leading off it.
# A [[restrict]]ed [[tract]] of [[land]] that allows passage between two places.
# [[Airspace]] restricted for the passage of [[aircraft]].

====Derived terms====
*the [[corridors of power]]
*[[w:Polish Corridor|Polish Corridor]]

